Somlet me tell you the story. About a yea ago, an old lady died. Apparently this lady was a real traveler andknew a lot of people, however all her stuff was practically thrown away I dont know why. My brothers and I began to dig inthethe pile of things and took a lot of it, among these things we found a lot of old discs, the lnes that can pnly be played in those old machines, phonographs. All of them were very old and inside of one of the discs I found a very old score signed with a lot of symbols, most of them unreadable but with the notes very much in good state. I can read notes and play the piano a little but considering what I saw it requires a much more talented player. Interested? Its called the "Tamborileo" or drumming.
